sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant FE as browser
    participant GW as api-gateway
    participant AUTH as orches-auth-service
    participant SVC as user-service
    participant DB as user-db
    participant R as Redis
    participant NOTIF as notification-service
    participant SES as amazon-ses

    Note over FE,SES: Pre-state: login:softlock:{userId} expired in Redis<br/>failed_login_attempts = 9 in DB   hard_locked = false

    rect rgb(240,248,255)
    Note over FE,SES: 1. Login & Pre-checks

    FE->>GW: POST /auth/login { email, password }
    GW->>AUTH: login({ email, password })
    AUTH->>SVC: find_user_by_email(email)
    SVC->>DB: SELECT id, is_email_verified, password_hash,<br/>failed_login_attempts, hard_locked<br/>FROM users WHERE email = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
    DB-->>SVC: { failed_login_attempts: 9, hard_locked: false, ... }
    SVC-->>AUTH: user

    alt user not found | not verified | hard_locked = true
        AUTH-->>GW: 401 Unauthorized
        GW-->>FE: 401 Unauthorized
    end

    AUTH->>R: EXISTS login:softlock:{userId}
    R-->>AUTH: 0 (no active soft lock)
    end

    rect rgb(255,248,235)
    Note over FE,SES: 2. Credential Validation

    Note over AUTH: bcrypt.compare(password, password_hash) → FAIL
    end

    rect rgb(255,220,220)
    Note over FE,SES: 3. Record Failed Attempt & Apply Hard Lock

    AUTH->>SVC: record_failed_attempt(user_id)
    SVC->>DB: UPDATE users<br/>SET failed_login_attempts = failed_login_attempts + 1,<br/>    last_failed_login_at = NOW(),<br/>    hard_locked = true<br/>WHERE id = ? RETURNING failed_login_attempts
    Note right of DB: Single atomic UPDATE — counter + hard_locked together<br/>Only password reset (LOG-08) clears hard_locked
    DB-->>SVC: { failed_login_attempts: 10, hard_locked: true }
    SVC-->>AUTH: { failed_login_attempts: 10, hard_locked: true }
    Note over R: No Redis write — hard lock lives in DB only (must survive restart)
    end

    rect rgb(240,255,245)
    Note over FE,SES: 4. Notify User

    AUTH-)NOTIF: emit('send_account_hard_lock_email') { to: user.email }
    Note right of NOTIF: Fire-and-forget ⚡<br/>⚠ New handler + template needed
    NOTIF->>SES: nodemailer.sendMail() via SMTP
    SES-->>NOTIF: 250 OK

    AUTH-->>GW: 401 { error_code: "HARD_LOCKED",<br/>message: "Account locked. Please reset your password to regain access." }
    GW-->>FE: 401 HARD_LOCKED
    Note over FE: UI: "Account locked" + "Reset password" link (→ LOG-08)
    end
